Quick cheatsheet (save this)

Service (backend Flask)

Get-Service vega-gateway
Start-Service vega-gateway
Restart-Service vega-gateway
Stop-Service vega-gateway
Get-Content C:\Vega\gateway.log -Tail 50


Tunnel (Cloudflare)

schtasks /Query /TN "vega-bridge" /V /FO LIST
schtasks /End /TN "vega-bridge"  | Out-Null
schtasks /Run /TN "vega-bridge"  | Out-Null


Public health checks

Invoke-WebRequest "https://bridge.cryptobitcoinprofits.com/health"
(Invoke-WebRequest -Uri "https://bridge.cryptobitcoinprofits.com/connect" `
  -Headers @{ Authorization = "Bearer 377c8012-5d62-4b32-9a10-973fcc581551" }).Content


Watcher (optional enhancement applied earlier)

If you updated the watcher to also start vega-gateway, you’re fully self-healing for both the tunnel and the backend.

If you want, I can add a one-liner to rotate the gateway.log daily or on size, but otherwise you’re good to go.
